1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the geometric representation and analysis of graphs made of curves and junctions, which falls under the scope of computational geometry. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper mentions various applications of the proposed framework, such as analyzing brain fiber tracts and arterial networks, which are relevant to computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the analysis of graphs, which can be considered as social and information networks. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper mentions the use of statistical tools such as principal component analysis and analytical statistical testing and modeling, which are commonly used in machine learning. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper mentions the use of efficient algorithms for computing mathematical representations and metrics, which falls under the scope of numerical analysis.
